cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.DL, cs.DB

The paper discusses a new knowledge representation and mining system that has applications in natural language processing, anomaly detection, data classification, and recommendation systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Deep Learning (cs.DL), and Databases (cs.DB). However, since the paper focuses on the representation and traversal of relationships between entities, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories.
